The scope of the disaster would seem to justify a temporary surcharge. The Legislature can begin organizing its staff and committees now so the appropriate legislation can be passed as soon as that information is obtained. The governor is wrong, however, in his campaign to distance himself from the California Department of Transportation on the issue of what caused the Nimitz Freeway in Oakland to collapse, and what could or should have been done to have prevented it. The state learns more from every earthquake and a critical need now is to learn everything possible from Tuesday, Oct 17. 